trend_summary: Across the time-series, the landscape stays overwhelmingly agricultural. Small clusters of farmsteads and scattered houses grow marginally, while several paddocks are either consolidated or replaced by young woodland blocks. Road traces and driveways multiply slightly, yet no large built-up core emerges. Overall change is slow and low-intensity, keeping the area largely rural and open.
notable_changes: Minor enlargement of several village or hamlet clusters along main roads.
Addition of new driveways and short road segments connecting isolated properties.
Consolidation of some small fields into larger pasture units through hedgerow removal.
Emergence of new plantation/woodlot patches, especially in northern hills.
Scattered new agricultural outbuildings appearing near existing farmyards.
